contentrichtext.text: '''DH''', '''Dh''' or '''dh''' may refer to: ==Flying== *[[de Havilland]], a former UK aircraft manufacturer *[[Decision height]], an element of aviational instrument approach *[[Independence Air]]'s IATA code ==Science and health== *[[Department of Health (United Kingdom)]], a branch of government *[[Dermatitis herpetiformis]], a skin disease *[[Doubled haploidy]], a genetic status ==Measurement== *[[Deutsche Härte]] (°dH), a measurement of hard water *[[DH register]], the high byte of an X86 16-bit DX register *[[Dirham]] **[[United Arab Emirates dirham]] ==Methods== * [[Diffie-Hellman key exchange]], a cryptographic protocol * [[Digital Humanities]], a community of practice combining technology with humanistic inquiry * [[District heating]], a method of heating multiple buildings from a central location ==Places== * [[DH postcode area]], in the United Kingdom * [[Diamond Head, Hawaii]] ==Sports== * [[Designated hitter]], a baseball rule * [[Downhill]], a skiing discipline * [[Downhill mountain biking]], a bicycling discipline ==Other uses== * [[Dear Husband]], a shorthand phrase common in online forums * ''[[The Deer Hunter]]'', a 1978 film * [[Delaware and Hudson Railway]] * [[Demon Hunter]], an American metal band * [[Denavit–Hartenberg parameters]], a type of robotics convention * ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'', an American television series * [[Dh (digraph)]], in linguistics * ''[[Die Hard]]'', a 1988 film starring [[Bruce Willis]] * [[Digital humanities]] * [[Dior Homme]], the menswear division of Dior * [[Documentary hypothesis]] * ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows]]'', as referred to by the fandom ==See also== *[[DH Press]] *[[David Hart Smith]] {{disambiguation}}
